	<item>
		<title>Get started with Viber Automation</title>
		<link>https://docs.chatrace.com/kb/viber-automation/</link>
					<comments>https://docs.chatrace.com/kb/viber-automation/#respond</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Team]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 08 Jun 2022 17:22:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://docs.chatrace.com/?post_type=kb&#038;p=2250</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Chatrace allows you to easily create Viber bots for free to automate conversations between your business and your customers. Unlike Messenger, WhatsApp, and Instagram which]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>Chatrace allows you to easily create Viber bots for free to automate conversations between your business and your customers. </p>



<p>Unlike Messenger, WhatsApp, and Instagram which have limitations on when you can send contacts a free broadcast messages (24h window), Viber doesn&#8217;t have any limitations on when you can send a contact a message. On the Viber channel, you can send a broadcast to your contact list any time for free.</p>



<p>All channels are available on our free plan including <strong>Viber</strong>. </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What you will need?</h3>



<p>In order to create a Viber bot, you will need to have a Viber account. To create a Viber account just Install the Viber app from <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.viber.voip&amp;hl=en&amp;gl=US" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Play Store</a> or <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/id382617920?mt=8" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Apple Store</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to create a Viber bot?</h3>



<p>1 &#8211; Create your Viber bot on Viber by clicking this <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://partners.viber.com/account/create-bot-account" target="_blank">link</a>. After you create your bot you will need to copy the bot token.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1024" height="975" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-2-1024x975.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2257" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-2-1024x975.png 1024w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-2-300x286.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-2-768x731.png 768w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-2.png 1360w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>2 &#8211; Go to <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://chatrace.com/en/new-bot" target="_blank">Chatrace</a> and choose the Viber channel.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="982" height="941" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2254" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image.png 982w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-300x287.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-768x736.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 982px) 100vw, 982px" /></figure>



<p>3 &#8211; Insert the <strong>Bot Token </strong>that you get in step 1 and click <strong>Continue</strong>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="903" height="731" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2255" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-1.png 903w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-1-300x243.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-1-768x622.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px" /></figure>



<p></p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">3 &#8211; How to create flows for Viber Channel?</h4>



<p>Go to Menu &gt; Flows and create a new flow. When creating flows always use the <strong>Omnichannel</strong> message type. Using <strong>Omnichannel</strong> will allow you to create a flow once and the same flow will work on all current and future channels if the elements that you use on your flows are compatible with other channels. Please what</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="503" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-3-1024x503.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2258" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-3-1024x503.png 1024w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-3-300x147.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-3-768x377.png 768w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-3-1536x755.png 1536w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-3.png 1919w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="How to create a basic conversation flow" width="780" height="439" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/IkU6_JnHabE?list=PLtVr4HgJMyadDeZn86_CjeoxyfOW5rza6" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<p></p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How to send a broadcast message?</h4>



<p>1 &#8211; Create the flow that you want to send.</p>



<p>2 &#8211; Go to Menu &gt; Broadcasts and click the <strong>Send</strong> button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="541" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-4-1024x541.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2259" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-4-1024x541.png 1024w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-4-300x159.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-4-768x406.png 768w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-4.png 1355w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>3 &#8211; Choose <strong>Viber</strong> as a <strong>Message Channel</strong> and select the flow you created in step 1.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="540" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-5-1024x540.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2260" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-5-1024x540.png 1024w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-5-300x158.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-5-768x405.png 768w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/image-5.png 1358w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p></p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">What data does Viber provide about a contact?</h4>



<p>Viber provides contact name, profile image language, and country. Please be aware that Viber contacts can opt to not share their data with a bot. </p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
